---

## Introduction

### Dandiset Overview

- **Title:** Hippocampal neuronal responses to programmable antigen-gated G-protein-coupled engineered receptor activation
- **DOI:** [10.48324/dandi.001354/0.250312.0036](https://doi.org/10.48324/dandi.001354/0.250312.0036)
- **Repository:** [DANDI Archive – DANDI:001354](https://dandiarchive.org/dandiset/001354/0.250312.0036)
- **License:** CC-BY-4.0

### Scientific Background

This Dandiset contains data from single-cell electrophysiological recordings of hippocampal CA1 neurons in mice, where neurons were genetically engineered to express programmable, antigen-gated G-protein-coupled engineered receptors (PAGERs). The purpose was to assess neuronal activity changes in response to activation of these engineered receptors, using pharmacological agents to manipulate GPCR signaling in a cell-type and condition-specific manner.

**Relevant Protocol:**  
- [Protocol publication in Nature](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-024-08282-3)

### Key Metadata

- **Species:** Mus musculus (House mouse)
- **Number of subjects:** 8
- **Number of cells/recordings:** 50
- **Number of NWB files:** 50
- **Data format:** Neurodata Without Borders (NWB)
- **Techniques:** Single-cell electrophysiology, current clamp
- **Variables measured:** CurrentClampSeries, CurrentClampStimulusSeries

### Acknowledgments

Funders include the National Institute of Mental Health, National Cancer Institute, Phil and Penny Knight Initiative for Brain Resilience, and others.  
Contact: Peter Klein (kleinp@stanford.edu)
